719196f-a.text:
Convent Avenue, east side, north across West 149th Street, showing at the right, the Cosmosolital Tennis Club. This is hidden behind the sign boards on the Avenue. View 2 is limited to the antrance between the billboards.
May 19, 1940
No's. 1-2
P. L. Sperr

719198f-a.text:
Convent Avenue, west side, from 150th to 149th Street. Hamilton Grange Reformed Church is at the left in the background. At the right is 450-460 West 150th Street, at adjoining, and west of the S.W. corner of Convent Avenue. The six houses comprising the numbers from 450-460 are all 3 1/2-story frame houses.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 376
